sql:
SELECT sport_id, COUNT(highlight_id) as total_highlights
   FROM highlights
   GROUP BY sport_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Highlights" refer to notable moments or clips from events;
- "Engagement" is measured by the total number of views on these highlights;
- "Top 5" means the sports with the highest engagement.

- "Top highlights" refers to the highlights with the highest score within each event;
- "Score" is a measure of popularity or quality, typically represented by upvotes or similar metrics;
- "Total number of highlights" is the count of all highlights associated with each event.

- "stand out like the peak of a mountain" refers to the top-scoring highlight;
- "score" is a measure of how well-received or popular the highlight is;
- Each event may have multiple highlights, but only the one with the highest score is selected.

- "crown jewel" refers to the sport with the highest number of comments;
- "shining brightest" refers to the sport that is most discussed or commented on;
- "realm of discussion" refers to the comments made on the highlights of the sports.

- "star of the show" refers to the sport with the highest average number of views per highlight;
- "shining brightest" refers to the sport that attracts the most attention, measured by the average number of views per highlight;
- "average number of views per highlight" is calculated by dividing the total number of views by the total number of highlights for each sport.

- "top highlights" refers to the highlights with the highest number of views within each sport, specifically the top 3;
- "most popular highlights" are determined by the number of views;
- "most popular sports" are those with the highest count of top highlights.

sql:
SELECT title, score
FROM highlights
ORDER BY score DESC;

SELECT title, score, highlight_type
FROM highlights
ORDER BY score DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "Stands tall" refers to the sport with the highest average score of its highlights;
- "Celebrated highlights" refers to highlights with high scores or upvote counts;
- "Measured by the highest average score" indicates the sport with the maximum average score among all sports.
